PrecisAuthority to enter into a SETTLEMENT AGREEMENT with the OCHAPOWACE INDIAN BAND which provides for the payment of compensation in respect of a specific claim arising from Treaty No. 4, to wit the surrender on June 30, 1919, of some 18,240 acres of Ochapowace Indian Reserve No. 71 in Saskatchewan that were subsequently sold to the Soldier Settlement Board.
